Mortgageport is the trading name of Mortgageport Management Pty Limited, an Australian company established in 1998. Mortgageport is a mortgage manager that accesses wholesale lending funds from three banks; it also markets and manages residential home loans to borrowers across Australia.
Mortgageport is located in Milsons Point, New South Wales, where it has been located since 1999. Established by Glen Spratt and Michael McKelvie, a 50% stake in the company was purchased in 2004 by the Over Fifties Group. In 2011 Spratt and McKelvie bought this 50% stake back.
In 2016 the company entered the Non Bank lending market, where they offer residential mortgage loans as the lender.
